         <abstract>
            <p>An automatic quadrature is presented for computing Cauchy principal value integrals $Q(f; c) = \not{\int}^b_a f(t)/(t - c)dt, a &lt; c &lt; b$, for smooth functions $f(t)$. After subtracting out the singularity, we approximate the function $f(t)$ by a sum of Chebyshev polynomials whose coefficients are computed using the FFT. The evaluations of $Q(f; c)$ for a set of values of $c$ in $(a, b)$ are efficiently accomplished with the same number of function evaluations. Numerical examples are also given.</p>
          </abstract>
